Class IRLRequest

    • burlap.behavior.singleagent.learnfromdemo.IRLRequest

    ApprenticeshipLearningRequest, MLIRLRequest

    public class IRLRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    A data structure for setting the common parameters necessary for an IRL algorithm.

    Stephen Brawner and Mark Ho

      • IRLRequest

        public IRLRequest()
        Values will not be initialized. You must use the setters for the domain, valueFunction, and expert episodes.

      • IRLRequest

        public IRLRequest(Domain domain,
          OOMDPPlanner valueFunction,
          java.util.List<EpisodeAnalysis> expertEpisodes)
        Initializes. Discount factor will be defaulted to 0.99, which can optionally be changed with a setter.
        Parameters:
        domain - the domain in which IRL is to be performed
        valueFunction - the planning algorithm the IRL algorithm will invoke.
        expertEpisodes - the example expert trajectories/episodes.
